				<h2>Answer</h2>
				<h3>Score ::5</h3>
				<p><p>Right on cue - a long discussion on how the  too chatty  standard was loose and unhelpful - <a href="https://meta.stackexchange.com/questions/292011/drop-not-constructive-combine-noisy-reword-rude-and-other-comment-flag">we ve done away with that flag across all sites effective immediately.</a></p>

<p><a href="https://i.stack.imgur.com/GxUfW.png" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><img src="https://i.stack.imgur.com/GxUfW.png" alt="rude or abusive, no longer needed, in need of moderator intervention"></a></p>

<h1>The problem</h1>

<p>Comments are terrible; no one agrees on what they're for, or how long they should be kept. Comment flags are equally terrible, because if no one's on the same page as far as what should be posted in the first place then no one can agree on what should be removed either. On top of that, we have this confusing set of flags where two mean "noise", one means "vile", one means "moderator, help!" and one means nothing at all - the end result is that it's all but impossible to even analyze comment flagging.</p>
</p><br>
